cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the ability of artificial neural networks to judge the grammatical acceptability of a sentence, which is a task related to natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper trains several recurrent neural network models on acceptability classification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the ability of artificial neural networks to perform a linguistic task. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper specifically focuses on artificial neural networks. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not seem to deal with complexity theory, but it is still a possible category as the paper may involve some computational complexity analysis of the models used.
